			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Aegis of Life is mine!!<BR>
<BR>
     Thanks to the assistance of a kindly bard my quest was abruptly cut short today.  He and I had spoken on a previous day.  He told me that he had stumbled across the Undead Grimrot at the skele playground a while back and that he had the heart.  We quickly travelled to the Temple of Life and raised his faction using themethod I described below and by performing the Koalndl fish quest (be warned: log an alt to kill the fish for they give bad faction to kill... loot them with your main to turn them in).  The bard hailed Camlend Serbold and Camlen asked him to perform the quest so we knew his faction was good.  MY friend then handed in the heart, I handed in the Scythe and Camlend gifted me with the Aegis!!  As a thank you for his efforts I gave the young bard my old back slot item, a Kunzar Cloak from Karnor's Castle.<BR>
     I had some competition from a couple of casters (cleric and druid) but they figured they had it timed and would only pop in occasionally.  Let me just say that I camped the spawn for 10hrs straight at a time and my persistence resulted in the scythe... and nothing beats a friend stumbling across the other half of the quest.  Good luck all, be well and do good things.<BR>
<BR>
***  Hammers High!!!  ***<BR>
